verbs.description: overgrow (third-person singular simple present overgrows, present participle overgrowing, simple past overgrew, past participle overgrown)

entries.meaning: (intransitive) To grow beyond one's boundaries or containment, or beyond the proper size.
(transitive) To grow over; (of one thing) to cause (a second thing) to become overgrown (with or by the first thing).
examples: "If there is ivy overgrowing things, then we shall clean it up."
